1. 26. ex deserto—insitus] Cic. is here ridiculing Atilius, who by means of arroyatia not unattended by fraud, had managed to get himself transferred from the qens Gavia into the Atilia. To this transitus in aliam ,qentem the term inseri is applied (in reference also to Serranus), in continuation of the metaphor, from husbandry. It is uncertain where Cic. makes Atilius come from, because the reading of the uss after deserto viz. 9a'violaeliorea is unintelligible. Halm follows Madvig in writing Gavii (Gavi) Oleli rure, as if to mark meta- phorically the decayed condition of some particular family.
